item.title: Simplest College Guide
item.description: Why are summers so short and school years so long? I’m sure you’re feeling a little sad about summer being over, a little nervous with a dash of excitement for the new school year to commence or you just don’t know how to feel right now and that’s okay too. I get it.

item.title: Why Finding A Church Took So Long
item.description: Since moving to America, I’ve gone through the process of finding a new church I can call home. I went through this process with my parents when I was 13. Eventually, we settled for a church and called it home since then. Until recently…

item.title: I said, Onto Better Things: 2016 Wrap Up
Christmas in Kansas 2016
item.description: Three days before Christmas 2016, G and I left Albuquerque to spend Christmas with his family in Kansas. We left around 21:00, making it the best decision ever because we missed all the weather!
